com.salesforce.omakase.parser.factory

Class BaseTokenFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.salesforce.omakase.parser.factory.BaseTokenFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TokenFactory
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StandardTokenFactory

    public class BaseTokenFactory
extends Object
implements TokenFactory
    Base class for TokenFactorys.

    Subclasses can override methods as appropriate to specify alternative or additional tokens to recognize as various delimiters.

      • specialDeclarationBegin

        public Optional<Token> specialDeclarationBegin()
        Description copied from interface: TokenFactory
        Gets the Token representing an optional special character that may appear before a normal property name in a Declaration.

        For example, to enable the star hack the "*" token could be returned. If overriding this method, consider using a CompoundToken of the super class implementation.

        Specified by:
        specialDeclarationBegin in interface TokenFactory
        Returns:
        The Token representing an optional special Declaration start character.
